    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-16T12:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-16T12:44:00-05:00" n="607"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.822/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-16T17:00:00-00:44"
                            >December 16, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 16—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Department’s telegram No. 37, December 11, 3 p.m.<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d607fn17">Not printed.</note> In connection with the Department’s
                    instruction No. 61, November 15, Liberian Government accepts counterproposals
                    but desires to know whether or no article 14 implies to waive port and harbor
                    dues on American vessels calling at Liberian ports and vice versa. If it does
                    not, Liberian Government is ready to conclude and sign commercial treaty.</p>
                <p>In connection with Department’s telegram No. 29, Nov. 18,<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d607fn19">Not printed.</note> Liberian Government has accepted
                        counterproposals.<note n="18" xml:id="d607fn18">Regarding consular
                        convention. See undated telegram No. 72 from the Minister in Liberia, <ref
                            target="#pg_811">p. 811</ref>.</note> I am awaiting instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
